properties.abstract: Tour within the Braunwald-Klausenpass holiday region and car-free Braunwald, offering unspoiled scenery and fresh mountain air. The views are spectacular as far as the eye can see - and whenever you need to stop for a breather.
properties.description:
At the starting point in Linthal the route begins on a paved road leading to Alp Fritern with grades of up to 20%. A challenging ride on a gravel road takes you up to 1599 m, the highest point of the tour. This is followed by a steep downhill section to Restaurant Nussbel. From Nssbel to Braunwald the trail continues through green forests, past old farmhouses with views of Ortstock and Tdi mountains.

The trail leads through the widely scattered village of Braunwald to Braunwaldalp-Unterstafel and passing blooming summer fields and alpine herders. At Bchialp you can quench your thirst and taste a piece of freshly made alpine cheese, before heading for a fast ride down the steep, but excellent mountain road. Through the woods offering views of the valley floor, the trail continues to Schwanden.
